main event: On January 25, 1962, a civilian astronomer observed four slow-moving objects in the sky over Miami, Florida.
interesting points: The objects were described as controlled and deliberate, unlike any known man-made craft., The objects appeared to be larger than the disk of Saturn when viewed through binoculars., Observers reported the objects moving in a northerly direction., The entire sighting lasted for approximately 20 seconds., The final conclusion categorizes the objects as unidentified.
sighted object: four diffuse-like objects in the sky
witness description: members of the Miami Astronomical Association and a civilian astronomer
